			<p>Mike, here&#8217;s a thought worth considering if it doesn&#8217;t stray too far from the topic at hand; one I had to face while preparing my presentation: I&#8217;m all for hacks like these, as they&#8217;re shamelessly easy to implement. </p>
<p>But are we ignoring the content-, context-, and feature-specific needs of mobile users? If I can afford only a few minutes to produce a mobilized version of my site, what&#8217;s presented here is excellent. But should it be used across the board, or should I first understand how/what/when mobile users will access my site, and then address the display issues once I understand that?</p>
<p>Regardless, resources like these can only help push us in the right direction regarding mobile web design. (And feel free to kill this comment if it&#8217;s too far off topic.)</p>

