		<li id="comment-6990" class="alt">
<div class="clearfix"><div class="avatarholder"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/bdde9b71abd5c42d628b7a1196430606?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahousebythepark.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FHouse%2Fimages%2Fgravatar_default.gif%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /></div>			<div class="commentauthor"><a href='http://www.sacramentoweb.org' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Justin Perkins</a> says:</div></div>
			
			<p>There should be no difference between those two variables, but I would use SERVER_NAME if anything just because that is the typical method of retrieving the domain name as typed in the browser.</p>
<p>You can see what this variable (along with many others) is set to by making a simple PHP page that looks like the following:</p>
<p>&lt;?php phpinfo(); ?&gt;</p>
<p> If you are seeing a difference between these two variables, your server may have a problem.</p>

			<div class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-6990" title="">#63</a> - July 22nd, 2005 at 12:27 am </div>


