<div class="clearfix"><div class="avatarholder"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/577ed5a9d1710e4fe095c8aeca5af4e3?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahousebythepark.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fthemes%2FHouse%2Fimages%2Fgravatar_default.gif%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' /></div>			<div class="commentauthor">John says:</div></div>
			
			<blockquote><p>preg_replace(&#8216;/&#62;\s+&#60;/&#8217;, &#8216;&#62;&#60;&#8217;</p></blockquote>
<p>If you simply strip out all whitespace between brackets, what happens when you get something like this:</p>
<p>&#60;b&#62;Something in bold&#60;/b&#62; &#60;i&#62;something in italics&#60;/i&#62;</p>
<p>it will come out as</p>
<p>something in boldsomething in italics.</p>
<p>which has bitten me before.</p>
<p>I think it&#8217;s safer to just reduce all runs of whitespace to a single space, unless you want to use a more complicated regex.</p>

