			<p>Hi Mike, I post my simple solution at the problem of set up subdomains that point to main site. It is probably the operation Dreamhost automatically makes. I have Cpanel and it works.<br />
The steps are:<br />
1. Create a subdomain &#8220;alfa&#8221; with your Control Panel<br />
2. if the directory&#8221;alfa&#8221; in your web space has been created, remove it<br />
3. Create symlink named &#8220;alfa&#8221; to public_html<br />
4. End.<br />
In Windows host, I don&#8217;t know if works.</p>

