			<p>Accessing mobile website using your computer:</p>
<p>If you like to access a mobile version of any website using your computer rather than your mobile phone, use the following link</p>
<p><a href="http://tiltview.com" rel="nofollow">http://tiltview.com</a></p>
<p>The website automatically directs you to a mobile version of the site you are trying to access. </p>
<p>You can also set your mobile phone type. I noticed if you select iPhone and enter facebook.com, you will be directed to <a href="http://iphone.facebook.com" rel="nofollow">http://iphone.facebook.com</a>.  But if you select Windows Mobile, you will be directed to <a href="http://m.facebook.com/?w2m" rel="nofollow">http://m.facebook.com/?w2m</a></p>

