			<p>Daniel and Damian: No idea. Maybe you are running PHP as CGI or something.  That would prevent the auto_prepend and auto_append functions from working.  All I can say is that the script is fine. If there&#8217;s something about your setup that isn&#8217;t allowing it to work, some Googling should eventually yield the problem. Also, make sure to manually add newlines and other special characters like quotes when you create your .htaccess file.  Copying and pasting from the web sometimes borks stuff.</p>

